comment: Lemma for ~ cantnf . Here we show existence of Cantor normal forms. Assuming (by transfinite induction) that every number less than ` C ` has a normal form, we can use ~ oeeu to factor ` C ` into the form ` ( ( A ^o X ) .o Y ) +o Z ` where ` 0 < Y < A ` and ` Z < ( A ^o X ) ` (and a fortiori ` X < B ` ). Then since ` Z < ( A ^o X ) <_ ( A ^o X ) .o Y <_ C ` , ` Z ` has a normal form, and by appending the term ` ( A ^o X ) .o Y ` using ~ cantnfp1 we get a normal form for ` C ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 28-May-2015.)
